			<h4>Week 17</h4>
			<p><b>Baby : </b>Now baby is developing to grow and practice reflexes they’ll need for life outside the womb.</p>
			<p>Like Sucking and swallowing reflexes  in order to get ready for the world outside the womb, and those first attempts at getting milk from the breast or the bottle. Some babies even begin to suck their thumbs in the womb.</p>
			<p>Baby swallow the amniotic fluid and excret it to urine into womb. </p>
			<p>Bone development: The cartilage in your 17-week fetus’ limbs has turned almost completely to bone. Their bones will continue to harden and fuse into their early years of life.</p>
			<p>Sweat glands:  Baby is developing sweat glands. Babies don’t actually sweat, though, until after they are born—and it can take a few weeks for all of the glands to start working.</p>
			<p>Your baby is making  fat tissue beneath the skin and Internal organs. Fat tissue has many important functions, such as storing energy, insulating the body, protecting the organs, and filling out the baby’s features.</p>
			<p><b>Umbilical cord:</b> The umbilical cord on baby at 17 weeks is getting longer and thicker, so it’ll be strong enough to keep up with all the demands of the second half of pregnancy. Think of the umbilical cord as a lifeline from mom to baby. It has a vein that carries blood filled with oxygen and nutrients to baby, and two arteries that send all the waste (like carbon dioxide) back to the placenta.</p>
			<p><b>Common Body Changes at 17 week </b></p>
			<p>You mostly may be feeling better in terms of morning sickness and nausea. Also, your body should feel little bit energetic. </p>
			<p>More importantly, you should have your bump in place.please to compare with other dont worry if bump not obvious at this time because the size of the bump is different for different women. </p>
			<p>Your tummy (abdomen)is trying  to adjust space for your baby so u may  feel somewhat uncomfortable, indigestion and heartburn.</p>
			<p>Constipation and gas problems will also see a rise during your 17th week of pregnancy</p>
			<p>Expect mood swings as your hormones go haywire.</p>
			<p>Changes in hormonal levels can cause pigmentation of the skin and this will start happening in the 17th week of pregnancy.</p>
			<p>Expect some nerve pain especially in your legs as your baby is getting heavier inside of you.</p>
			<p>Now as the pregnancy advances blood volume increases which increases Extra work load to Your heart to supply the two of you. The increased volume of blood circulating between mom and baby may cause swelling, dizziness, bleeding gums, or nosebleeds. Some you may feel palpitations feeling increased heart beat. </p>
			<p>At this stage some women note increased sweating and large amounts of clear or creamy-white vaginal discharge, which is normal. </p>
			<p>There may be varicose veins in your legs, or you may have  hemorrhoids. Greater volumes of blood and more abundant circulation in the pelvis cause veins to swell and dilate. To prevent hemorrhoids and other unpleasant pregnancy symptoms, doctors recommend low-intensity exercise, prenatal yoga or swimming, more fresh-air walks, sufficient water intake, and a balanced diet.</p>

			<p><b>Tests at 17 week</b></p>
			<p>There are two types of tests, screening test and diagnostic test.</p>
			<p>Screening test as done at end of 1st trimester are double marker, nuchal translucency with other sonomarkers on ultrasound and nipt that we discussed previously.</p>
			<p>Now we discuss diagnostic tests done	Between Between 16 and 20 weeks.</p>
			<p>What’s the difference? A screening tells you percentage of the risk factor of your baby having a condition, and a diagnostic test tells you whether they actually have it.</p>
			<p>Screenings, like a nuchal translucency, Diagnostic tests, like amniocentesis, CVS or cordocentesis, have confirmed results.As the diagnostic usually are invasive. In other words, they may have to take your blood, amniotic fluid or even blood from the umbilical cord for testing. Some diagnostic tests come with risks, so many parents-to-be opt not to do them unless a screening test suggests there could be an issue or there’s family history of a genetic condition.</p>
			<p>Other test are very important to check your health and wel being</p>
